<li><strong>Local Utility Programs:</strong> Smaller municipal utilities throughout New Hampshire offer their own incentive programs, including rebates for energy-efficient appliances and sometimes additional support for solar installations. These programs vary by utility and should be researched based on specific service territories.</li>
<li><strong>USDA Rural Energy Grants:</strong> Rural properties in New Hampshire may qualify for USDA Rural Energy for America Program (REAP) grants, which can cover up to 25% of project costs for renewable energy installations, including solar panels and energy-efficient HVAC systems.</li>
</ul>

